  <section class="pt-0">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12">
          <div id="accordion" class="accordion style-2">
            <div class="card active">
              <div class="card-header">
                <h6 class="mb-0">
                  <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse1" aria-expanded="false" class="collapsed"><span></span>What information do we collect?</a>
                </h6>
              </div>
              <div id="collapse1" class="collapse show" data-parent="#accordion" style="">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <p class="text-justify">We use different methods to collect personal information from and about you including:</p>
                  <p class="text-justify">Personal information you give us. You may give us your personal information including name and contact details, by filling in forms or by corresponding with us by post, phone, email or otherwise. This includes personal information you provide when you ask us about, or apply for, our products or services; subscribe to our services or publications; request marketing to be sent to you or give us some feedback. Although some of the features of our Service may not require any registration, in order to use the full scope of this web site, a user must first sign up (we might decide to require registration to other parts of the Service in the future). During registration a user is required to give certain information such as your email, name, etc.</p>
                  <p class="text-justify">Some information is being collected automatically. For example, we collect diagnostic, performance and maintenance information about your activity, your use of the Services, log files and other reports. We also collect device-specific information when you use the Services.</p>
                  <p class="text-justify">This may include information such as your mobile device type, operating system information, browser information, IP addresses and network information including device identifiers. If you use location features, we may collect device location information.</p>

                  <h5 id="cookie-policy">Cookies</h5>
                  <p class="text-justify">If you have paid for any of our Services, we may receive payment information such as credit cards details, billing address etc., as well as other information and confirmations, such as payment receipts, including from app stores or other third parties (including payment solutions providers) processing your payment.</p>
                  <p class="text-justify">We use cookies to operate, improve and customize the Services and to improve your experience. A cookie is a small text file that a website you visit asks your browser to store on your computer or mobile device. </p>
                  <p class="text-justify">We may also use cookies to show you relevant content related to the Services. Finally, we may use cookies to remember your preferences, such as language and other choices you made using our Services. You can follow the instructions on your browser or device in order to control your cookie settings. Please note that if you set your browser or device to disable cookies (in whole or in part), certain of our Services may not function properly or at all.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-header">
                <h6 class="mb-0">
                  <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2" aria-expanded="false" class="collapsed"><span></span>How do we process personal information?</a>
                </h6>
              </div>
              <div id="collapse2" class="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" style="">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <p class="text-justify">We use the information we collect about you mainly in order to provide you with our Services, to improve them, to customize them to your specific needs, to perform support and maintenance to our Services, to develop new services and features, to monitor and protect the security of our information, systems and network and to market our Services so you and your connections can have a more enjoyable and rewarding experience.</p>
                  <p class="text-justify">We also use your information to communicate with you regarding the Services, respond to you when you contact us, let you know about updates to our Services or to our Terms and other important updates.</p>
                  <p class="text-justify">Please note that we may also use your information if we believe that it is reasonably required to be compliant with any applicable laws or regulations, court orders or other legal proceedings, requests from governmental entities, to enforce our Terms and polices, to investigate and prevent fraud or other illegal activity or for other security or technical issues including without limitations to protect you and our other users.</p>
                  <p class="text-justify">Unless you ask us not to, we may contact you via email in the future to tell you about specials, new products or services, or changes to this privacy policy. We will ask for your consent to receive marketing communications in line with the applicable law when you first provide your personal information.</p>
                  <p class="text-justify">In case we will allow any third-party ads on the Services or any other commercial content, we will make sure this is done in compliance with applicable laws and regulations.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-header">
                <h6 class="mb-0">
                  <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse3" aria-expanded="false" class="collapsed"><span></span>Sharing your personal information</a>
                </h6>
              </div>
              <div id="collapse3" class="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" style="">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <p class="text-justify">We share your information mainly as reasonably necessary in order to provide you with our Services, to improve them, to customize them to your specific needs, to perform support and maintenance to our Services, to develop new services and features and to market our Services so you and your connections can have a more enjoyable and rewarding experience. </p>
                  <p class="text-justify">We do our best efforts to make sure that the third parties we share your information with will safeguard your information using measures which are at least as protective to your privacy as the measures we are using. We also require that such third parties will use your information in accordance with privacy and data protection policies which are at least as protective as our policies.</p>
                  <p class="text-justify">We may share and transfer your information to our affiliates and related entities or to any other third party in connection with a merger, consolidation, restructuring, acquisition of our shares or assets or any other change of control transaction, whether by operation of law or otherwise. We also may share and transfer your information to relevant third parties such as consultants and advisors as part of an initial public offering.</p>
                  <p class="text-justify">We may share and transfer your information to our affiliates and related entities or to any other third party in connection with a merger, consolidation, restructuring, acquisition of our shares or assets or any other change of control transaction, whether by operation of law or otherwise. We also may share and transfer your information to relevant third parties such as consultants and advisors as part of an initial public offering.</p>
                  <p class="text-justify">Last, we may reasonably share information with third parties in connection with our use of your information as set forth in this Privacy Policy (e.g. for legal purposes, enforcing the Terms, prevent legal activities, protect our users, etc.).</p>
                  <p class="text-justify">We do not allow our third-party service providers to use your personal information for their own purposes and only permit them to process your personal information for specified purposes and in accordance with our instructions.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-header">
                <h6 class="mb-0">
                  <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse4" aria-expanded="false" class="collapsed"><span></span>How we store your data</a>
                </h6>
              </div>
              <div id="collapse4" class="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" style="">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <p class="text-justify">Your personal data and its security is taken very seriously by us and so we use all reasonable efforts to ensure appropriate security measures to protect it. However, there is no way to guarantee 100% protection to information which is being transmitted via the internet.. Please note however, that we will follow strict procedures to protect your data and prevent unauthorized access.</p>
                  <p class="text-justify">The data we collect from you is stored in a fully PCI-DSS compliant data center located in Europe, which is protected by the strictest securities policies and measures. </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-header">
                <h6 class="mb-0">
                  <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse5" aria-expanded="false" class="collapsed"><span></span>How long do we keep your personal information?</a>
                </h6>
              </div>
              <div id="collapse5" class="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" style="">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <p class="text-justify">We will store your personal information, in a form which permits us to identify you, for no longer than is necessary for the purpose for which the personal information is processed.  We use your personal information as necessary to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements and rights, or if it is not technically and reasonably feasible to remove it.  Otherwise, we will seek to delete your personal information within a reasonable timeframe upon request.</p>
                </div>
